        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 3:58PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ballinger, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ballinger, Hatchel, Benoit, Rowena, The Intersection Of Us-
83 And Ranch Road 1929, Ballinger Lake, and Us-83 Near The Concho-
Runnels County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
